s well as satellites with significantly lower stellar mass\ncontent (30%). Finally, we find a slight difference between the formation times\nof the haloes which are younger in voids than the average population. These\ncharacteristics indicate that haloes populating voids have had a different\nformation history, inducing significant changes on the halo occupation\ndistribution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 Mar 2020 13:09:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-01"}
